{"article_id":"JlPUhxBJQrK76Ocy","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Story highlights","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"House Republicans argue for and against legal status for undocumented immigrants","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"GOP legislators say","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"work on immigration measures will likely go on for months","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"Former President Bush calls for a solution in a rare comment on a political issue","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"GOP leaders refuse to hold a vote on a Senate version","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"that passed with bipartisan support","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"Immigration reform entered an uncertain new phase on Wednesday","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"as House Republicans signaled some willingness to compromise with President Barack Obama and Democrats","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"but rejected a Senate-passed bill","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"and insisted","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"they would take their time","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"drafting their own version .","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"Following more than two hours of talks on how to proceed ,","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"GOP legislators said","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"the biggest question was whether to give the 11 million immigrants","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"living illegally in the United States","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"a path to eventual citizenship ,","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"as provided by the Senate measure .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"Participants in the Republican caucus meeting described a 50-50 split over the undocumented immigrant issue , with more consensus on the need","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"to produce some kind of legislation","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"to show the party 's commitment","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"to fixing a broken system","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"and addressing concerns of Hispanic Americans","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"-- the nation 's largest minority demographic .","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"Despite the divisions on the undocumented immigrant issue , House Majority Leader Eric Cantor of Virginia told the GOP members","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"that children","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"living illegally in the United States","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"through no fault to their own","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"should receive legal status .","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"House Judiciary Chairman Bob Goodlatte said","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"he and fellow Virginia Republican Cantor were working together on a bill","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"focused on children ,","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"which is a priority of Democrats","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"pushing for immigration reform .","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"Bush :","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"The immigration system is broken","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"Bush :","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"The immigration system is broken","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"01:46","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"JUST WATCHED Inside Man :","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"Life of a migrant farmer","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"MUST WATCH Inside Man : Life of a migrant farmer","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"00:58","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"Next step for immigration overhaul ?","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"MUST WATCH Next step for immigration overhaul ?","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"02:11","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"At the same time , House GOP leaders made clear","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"they intended to slow the process down","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"by tackling individual components of the broad measure","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"passed by the Democratic-led Senate last month with bipartisan support .","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"That means taking up smaller bills on specific provisions , such as border security and employment verification measures , in coming months","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"while also seeking a compromise within the caucus","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"on providing legal status for undocumented immigrants .","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"House Speaker John Boehner warned his caucus","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"that Republicans would face political attacks","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"if they failed to move legislation ,","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"according to several GOP sources in the room .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"`` We do n't want the White House to hope","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"that we fail to make it a campaign issue , ''","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"said GOP Rep. Michael McCaul of Texas .","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"`` House Republicans want to do this on our terms , and not on the Senate 's terms and not on the White House terms . ''","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"Another prominent House GOP leader , Budget Committee Chairman Rep. Paul Ryan of Wisconsin , told his colleagues","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"that doing nothing was not an option .","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"The unsuccessful Republican vice presidential nominee in last year 's election , Ryan made the case","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"also pushed by the White House","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"that immigration reform would help boost the American economy ,","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"participants said .","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"Meanwhile , a group of bipartisan House legislators","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"trying to draft its own immigration measure","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"met for several hours on Tuesday night","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"and would continue its work ,","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"said Democratic Rep. Xavier Becerra of California .","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"The group is working on a comprehensive bill closer in form to the Senate measure","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"and Becerra argued","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"the incremental approach","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"advocated by House Republicans","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"would n't work .","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"`` It 's better to eat your Wheaties","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"and do it right","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"than do it poorly","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"and 5-10 years from now have to come back at it again , ''","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"Becerra said .","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"The 1,000-plus page Senate immigration bill","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"passed last month","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"takes a comprehensive approach","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"that removes the threat of immediate deportation for most undocumented immigrants","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"and provides a path to legal status and eventual citizenship .","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"It also includes stronger enforcement provisions","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"including the virtual militarization of the Mexican border with almost double the agents , new technology and a longer fence ,","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"as well as requiring employers to verify the immigration status of workers and improved monitoring of visa holders .","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"While the Senate measure passed 68-32 with support from 14 Republicans ,","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"House GOP leaders insist","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"they will not bring it up","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"because most of their caucus opposes it .","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"Boehner has repeatedly said","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"any immigration bill","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"brought up for a House vote","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"must have support from a majority of Republicans ,","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"and he repeated that guarantee to his GOP caucus on Wednesday .","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"Democrats called on Boehner to allow a House vote on the Senate version ,","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"believing","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"it could pass with unified Democratic support along with several dozen Republicans .","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"Rep. Steny Hoyer of Maryland , the No . 2 Democrat in the House , said Wednesday","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"that Republicans were `` splintered and confused '' on immigration ,","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"describing what he called a `` deeply divided party ''","depth":8},{"id":112,"text":"that was `` much more into ideology","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"than they are into solving problems . ''","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"The immigration issue will be significant in next year 's congressional elections ,","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"with House Republicans under pressure from conservatives","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"to oppose what the political right-wing calls amnesty in the form of a path to legal status and even citizenship for people","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"who sneaked into the country illegally or overstayed their visas .","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"`` Once you start down that line ,","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"you 're destroying the rule of law , ''","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"conservative GOP Rep. Steve King of Iowa said after Wednesday 's caucus meeting .","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"He and fellow conservative Rep. Michele Bachmann of Minnesota described the GOP caucus as evenly divided on the question .","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"`` The real issue is amnesty .","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"The whole game is about legalization , the status of legalization , ''","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"Bachmann said .","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"On the other side was Rep. Ileana Ros-Lehtinen , a Cuban immigrant from Miami ,","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"who told reporters","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"that `` we have different points of view . '' `` I hope","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"we can also look at the 11 million people","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"who want to legalize their status , ''","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"she added .","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"For Obama and Democrats , passage of immigration reform would mean following through on a promise to the nation 's largest minority demographic","depth":7},{"id":132,"text":"-- Hispanic Americans --","depth":7},{"id":133,"text":"to reduce uncertainty for millions of them","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"living illegally in the United States .","depth":7},{"id":135,"text":"Moderate Republicans ,","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"including most of the party 's leaders in Congress ,","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"want a compromise","depth":7},{"id":138,"text":"that would represent a potential breakthrough for the GOP with Hispanics","depth":7},{"id":139,"text":"who voted overwhelmingly for Obama in last year 's election .","depth":7},{"id":140,"text":"Earlier Wednesday , former President George W. Bush added his voice to calls for a solution ,","depth":7},{"id":141,"text":"telling a ceremony for new citizens","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"that the present system was broken .","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"`` I do hope","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"there is a positive resolution to the debate , ''","depth":11},{"id":145,"text":"Bush said in a rare public comment about politics","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"since he left office .","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"While he refrained from taking sides ,","depth":11},{"id":148,"text":"he sounded moderate","depth":12},{"id":149,"text":"in saying","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"he hoped","depth":14},{"id":151,"text":"that `` we keep a benevolent spirit in mind . ''","depth":14},{"id":152,"text":"`` We understand the contributions","depth":13},{"id":153,"text":"immigrants make to our country , ''","depth":13},{"id":154,"text":"said Bush , a Republican .","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"`` We must remember","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"that the vast majority of immigrants are decent people","depth":13},{"id":157,"text":"who work hard","depth":14},{"id":158,"text":"and support their families","depth":15},{"id":159,"text":"and practice their faith","depth":16},{"id":160,"text":"and lead responsible lives . ''","depth":16},{"id":161,"text":"However , conservatives fear","depth":7},{"id":162,"text":"that legalizing undocumented immigrants means guaranteeing future electoral hardship for Republicans","depth":8},{"id":163,"text":"by adding millions of new voters","depth":9},{"id":164,"text":"who generally lean Democratic .","depth":9},{"id":165,"text":"The White House sought to keep up pressure on House Republicans ,","depth":9},{"id":166,"text":"asserting Wednesday","depth":10},{"id":167,"text":"that the Senate immigration measure would boost the U.S. economy","depth":11},{"id":168,"text":"and help create jobs .","depth":11},{"id":169,"text":"A Congressional Budget Office report","depth":13},{"id":170,"text":"released in June","depth":13},{"id":171,"text":"indicated","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"the Senate bill could reduce deficits by $ 175 billion over the first 10 years and by at least $ 700 billion in the second decade .","depth":11},{"id":173,"text":"The CBO ,","depth":13},{"id":174,"text":"working with the congressional Joint Committee on Taxation ,","depth":13},{"id":175,"text":"estimated","depth":12},{"id":176,"text":"that eight million unauthorized residents would become legal in the first decade .","depth":11},{"id":177,"text":"In addition , the CBO report estimated","depth":10},{"id":178,"text":"the bill would boost the U.S. population by a net of 10.4 million people by 2023 and by 16 million by 2033 .","depth":10},{"id":179,"text":"`` The benefits are clear .","depth":10},{"id":180,"text":"The fact","depth":12},{"id":181,"text":"that there is a broad bipartisan consensus behind this","depth":12},{"id":182,"text":"is clear , ''","depth":11},{"id":183,"text":"White House spokesman Jay Carney said Wednesday .","depth":9},{"id":184,"text":"`` It can not be acceptable , broadly and in the long term , that immigration reform would be blocked","depth":11},{"id":185,"text":"because some minority of House Republicans is concerned about a primary challenge from the far right .","depth":11},{"id":186,"text":"That 's not a good argument .","depth":11},{"id":187,"text":"It 's not a good argument politically .","depth":12},{"id":188,"text":"It 's certainly not a good argument economically , ''","depth":12},{"id":189,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":190,"text":"On the House side , the bipartisan group","depth":12},{"id":191,"text":"working on an immigration package","depth":12},{"id":192,"text":"would require","depth":11},{"id":193,"text":"that border security measures be in place","depth":11},{"id":194,"text":"before any process toward residency for undocumented immigrants could begin .","depth":11},{"id":195,"text":"`` The American people want our border secured ,","depth":11},{"id":196,"text":"our laws enforced ,","depth":13},{"id":197,"text":"and the problems in our immigration system fixed","depth":13},{"id":198,"text":"to strengthen our economy , ''","depth":12},{"id":199,"text":"said a joint statement by House GOP leaders","depth":11},{"id":200,"text":"that expressed distrust in Obama and Democrats","depth":13},{"id":201,"text":"to fully enact tougher security laws","depth":13},{"id":202,"text":"before legalizing undocumented immigrants .","depth":12},{"id":203,"text":"GOP Republican Rep. Darrell Issa of California told reporters","depth":10},{"id":204,"text":"the end result in the House would be `` fully comprehensive immigration reform ''","depth":11},{"id":205,"text":"that would address undocumented immigrants .","depth":11},{"id":206,"text":"He outlined legislation","depth":11},{"id":207,"text":"that would provide some with legal status , such as those","depth":13},{"id":208,"text":"who served in the military","depth":13},{"id":209,"text":"and children of undocumented immigrants","depth":13},{"id":210,"text":"brought into the country illegally by their parents .","depth":13},{"id":211,"text":"While other immigrants also could be considered for legal status ,","depth":12},{"id":212,"text":"those with criminal records should be kicked out ,","depth":12},{"id":213,"text":"Issa said .","depth":11},{"id":214,"text":"Sticking points in the House debate include whether undocumented immigrants would be eligible for health care benefits during the years","depth":9},{"id":215,"text":"it would take","depth":10},{"id":216,"text":"to get legal status ,","depth":10},{"id":217,"text":"and empowering state and local police to work with federal authorities","depth":9},{"id":218,"text":"in enforcing immigration laws .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":437,"left":0,"right":436,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":436,"left":270,"right":435,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":270,"left":224,"right":269,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":224,"left":222,"right":223,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":222,"left":221,"right":4,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":221,"left":1,"right":220,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":220,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":223,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":269,"left":251,"right":268,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":251,"left":235,"right":250,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":235,"left":229,"right":234,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":229,"left":7,"right":228,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":228,"left":8,"right":227,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":227,"left":9,"right":226,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":226,"left":10,"right":225,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":225,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":234,"left":230,"right":233,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":230,"left":13,"r